\begin{remark}[Why a "curved theory"?]
Usually, the field strength $F$ is given by (abelian, for simplicity)
\bas
F
&\coloneqq
\mathrm{d}A
=
\mathrm{d}^{\nabla^0}A.
\eas
$\rightsquigarrow$ We will use a general connection $\nabla$ instead of $\nabla^0$, and $\nabla$ may not be flat.
\end{remark}
	
